The paper proposes a new approach for generating object proposals using a discriminative convolutional network. This approach is related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.CV and cs.LG, respectively. The paper also introduces a new objective function for training the model, which involves predicting a class-agnostic segmentation mask and an object likelihood score. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), which are concerned with developing and improving ML algorithms. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several benchmark datasets, which indicates that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (multimedia). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
